#import "../../lib.typ": chapter

#chapter(8, "nice to meet you mikoutayapper, i am nagi seishiro")[
  After everything that happened, Mona found herself at the fastfood restaurant
  near her school.

  School ended, but unlike usual, Mona did not head straight to home. She was
  now sitting with two of her new friends: Nanba Mikoto and Kazugai Uta.

  When the bell rang, the two invited Mona out for a "light after-school meal",
  whatever that might mean. Mona, clearly interested in the whole ordeal, joined
  in without any reluctance.

  _"There was a show that Miyu-tan starred tonight... I'm sorry, Miyutan!"_

  Because three is an odd number, and three girls sitting on one side of the
  table would be weird, two girls would have to share a side.

  Which is actually perfect: Mona, the type of girl who needed personal space
  and was not particularly close to the other two, should sat on one side, while
  the other two happily chatted with on the other side.

  That was what Mona thought.

  And it could not be any further from what Mikoto had in mind.

  The one who was getting a side for her own was Uta, since Mikoto was having an
  unhealthy obsession with her new test subject, I mean, _friend_. Though, she
  definitely tried her best not to bother Mona too much.

  Mikoto continued the stream of questions she had for Mona. And Mona was
  attentively listening and answering Mikoto's questions, while actually asking
  some questions herself. That was definitely an improvement!

  "No way! You followed Miyu-tan too? We have so much in common!"

  "Hehe..." Mona grinned.

  This was not a mere coincidence, of course. Which the girl on the opposite
  side, seemed to notice.

  _"Most of Mikoto's knowledge of idols come from the reposts that Narumi Sena
  made. And Narumi Sena probably does not have much time to stalk idols, which
  means only one thing..."_

  Yes, it all came from Mona.

  Sena, with her current load of work, had no time to discover new idols. She
  just reposted what her sister liked. So in a way, everything that Mikoto knew
  all originated from Mona.

  Though, Uta was different. She had watched idols since she was young, and her
  idol knowledge did not come from one source. Though, lately, she could barely
  find the time to watch idols as much as she used to.

  She was very curious about Narumi Mona, however.

  _"This girl is the teacher of her sister, which is also the teacher of Mikoto.
  So she should have an extreme amount of knowledge... I want to chat with her,
  too."_

  But she found it hard to jump into the conversation. The scene in front of
  her was like a yuri couple, to some extent.

  "Mona! I'm glad that you are here. Y'know, Uta is always so so so busy, she
  would never spend much time talking to me about this stuff."

  "Hey! I had to spend all that time with your silly detective game, Mikoto.
  What do you mean by that?"

  And thus, Uta joined in the conversation. She had been looking at her
  smartphone, so she did not notice that Mikoto was paying attention to her,
  realizing how Uta was hesitant to talk to the other two.

  // if so, why did she blurt out that utasama like idols?
  // does uta feel uncomfortable because of that
  // well tbh i can just let it be because she was too excited to think or sth
  Mikoto might act reserved in front of strangers, but she was really mindful of
  people she deeply cared about.

  // A-san and B-san cameo lmfao (still temp names)
  "Hey, Mona! You've ever heard of A-san? I've been seeing videos of her
  on my feeds recently." Uta suddenly asked.

  _"Let's see how well-versed this girl really is... This idol is somewhat
  obscure, but she probably can nail this down easily."_

  Now that Uta had conveniently joined in the conversation, she could now
  ask some question to satisfy her curiosity.

  "Uhm... I saw her a couple of times on TV, but she is not really my type..."
  Mona answered, seemingly apologetic.

  It seemed that Mona misunderstood that A-san was someone Uta was
  following, even though Uta explicitly mentioned that she just stumble upon
  her.

  Noticing that, Uta immediately cleared up the confusion.

  "It's not like I like her or anything, y'know, but yesterday I saw her
  collaborating with B-san, so I'm somewhat intrigued. Oh, you know
  her?"

  Himeno Sena 2 was somewhat much more obscure than Himeno Sena 1, hence being
  the second challenge Uta had for Mona. If Mona knew her, she would actually be
  impressed.

  Mona nodded.

  _"Wow, color me surprised. She actually knew her."_

  Unlike A-san who had been maintaining a pretty consistent uploading
  schedule, B-san's appearances were all over the places. However, the
  most dedicated idol fans could easily understand why: A-san had no particular
  talent, so she had to be more active in order to stay relevant, though B-san,
  a hidden gem who was steadily rising in the shadows, were taking too many gigs
  that she could not announce publicly to her fans.

  Hence, anyone who knew B-san must be pretty well-versed.

  "... I went to her show once. It was truly unforgettable."

  // pj escape reference btw
  _"What? Going to her show? She meant that live at Kurume?"_

  Uta had never gone to an idol performance, so everything she knew was taken
  from the Internet or on TV. And now, in front of her was a guru who had
  experience travelling all across the nation to see idols.

  "I gave up." Uta muttered, bowing to Mona.

  "Eh?" Mona worriedly replied "Did I say something?"

  "Mona, she was just testing you." Mikoto, who had been listening to the
  conversation without understanding anything, interjected. "And it seemed you
  far surpassed her expectation."

  She glanced back to Uta, as if mocking her.

  "Is it that obvious?"

  "Yes, it is." Mikoto replied, "A-san and B-san? If those names don't exhibit
  extreme levels of obscurity, then I don't know what does."

  Though, to Mona, it was not that obvious. Especially as A-san and B-san was
  not that _obscure_ to begin with. There were plenty of other girls who were
  much better, anyway.

  "Well, this idol talk is making me tired. Especially because of a certain
  _someone_. So why don't we talk about something else?"

  "I thought you only cared about Mona because of idol stuff." Uta responded.

  "No, I did NOT. I said I'm going to be her friend, not her idol discipline!
  Ah, how about club stuff? You two gonna join any clubs?"

  "I'll pass, thanks." Uta immediately replied.

  "I expected that, but Mona?"

  "Probably the same for me."

  Mikoto let of a breath of disappointment. Why couldn't her friends be more
  enthuastic about such exciting things...

  "You two knew youth only comes once right?"

  "Right..."
]
